.TH TWU-CTL-NOTIFY 1 "2026-05-07" "0.1.0" "Tumbleweed Updater"
.SH NAME
twu-ctl-notify \- Tumbleweed Updater background notification helper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B twu-ctl-notify
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B twu-ctl-notify
is invoked by the systemd user timer
.B tumbleweed-updater-check.timer
to perform a background update check and notify the user
if updates are available.
.PP
If the Tumbleweed Updater GUI is already running,
.B twu-ctl-notify
exits silently \(em the GUI tray handles notification in that case.
.PP
To avoid notification spam,
.B twu-ctl-notify
records the last notified update count and only sends a new
notification when the count changes.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Always exits with status 0 to prevent systemd from marking
the service as failed on transient errors such as network
unavailability.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/TumbleweedUpdater/last-notified-count
Stores the update count from the last notification to prevent
duplicate notifications across timer runs.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tumbleweed-updater (1),
.BR twu-ctl (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
